instruction:
The bottom of a triangular prism is a right triangle with legs of 3 feet and 4 feet. Each solid is colored with a shade of green so that it is possible to cut into a number of smaller identically colored prisms by constructing cuts that are parallel to one of the sides and that coincide with the corners of the larger prism. How many smaller identical prisms?

[asy]
size(100);
import math;
vincolor="lightblue";
makegreen(v)--d--(a,0,0)--c--(a,-4,0)--b--(a,-3,0)--b1--(a,-4,0)--cycle;
makegreen(b)--b1--(c,0,0)--b1;
makegreen(b1)--a--(c,0,0)--d;
draw(b1--(c,0,0)--(d));
draw(a--(b)--(d)--cycle);
draw(b1);
draw(c++(0,0,4)--d++(0,0,4)--a++(0,0,4)--c);
draw(sticksurep(4));

[/asy]
